dct_description_sm: This line data layer represents railroad lines for the Upper Midwest in 2010. The Upper Midwest includes: Indiana, Illinois, Michigan, Minnesota, Ohio, and Wisconsin. The dataset was originally published by the Federal Railroad Administration in 2010.[The Rail Network is a comprehensive database of the nation's railway system at the 1:100,000 scale or better. The data set covers all 50 States plus the District of Columbia.]
